The paper deals with the extraction of unsatisfiable cores (UCs) for LTL, which is a topic related to logic and automated reasoning. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the implementation of the approach in a solver, which involves artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also deals with propositional LTL, which is a subfield of programming languages (cs.PL). The optimization of resolution graphs is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS), and the experimental evaluation involves measuring run time and memory usage, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
